    "IntroductionCausal graphs are integral to a variety of fields such as healthcare, statistics, economics, law, and business.",
    "They find applications in evaluation of drug efficacy, understanding effects of public policies, optimizing business decisions, and more [10].",
    "This is known as causal inference [15].A major issue with causal graphs is that they require human domain experts to generate them, but such experts are not always easily accessible.",
    "Thus, several algorithms have been conceived to automate their creation.",
    "This is commonly known as causal discovery [17]."
